CYSE 460: Power Systems and Smart Grid Security. 3 credits.
Covers fundamentals of power systems; basics of electricity, electricity generation, economics of supply and demand, and electricity market operations in regulated and deregulated environment. The other part of the course will cover Smart Grid and its impact on the energy industry. Also includes Energy policy modeling and analysis. Offered by Cyber Security Engineering. Limited to two attempts.
