Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

CYSE 462: Mobile Devices and Network Security. 3 credits.
Embedded security features of hand-held wireless devices. Data link layer encryption and authentication protocols applied in mobile devices. Security factors in the decisions on configuring wireless mobile devices and network infrastructure. Robust cryptography that is needed to attain the highest levels of integrity, authentication, and confidentiality. Offered by Cyber Security Engineering. Limited to two attempts.
