CYSE 580: Hardware and Cyber Physical Systems. 3 credits.
Covers computer architecture and hardware to support subsequent cyber-physical systems modules. Introduces cyber-physical systems as an integration of physical processes, computation, and networking. Discusses modeling and simulation of cyber-physical systems, system design, and implementation. Covers security issues in cyber-physical systems and applications selected from infrastructure, energy, transportation, robotics, manufacturing, and communications domains. Students study and build cyber-physical systems. Offered by Cyber Security Engineering. May not be repeated for credit.
Registration Restrictions: Enrollment limited to students with a class of Advanced to Candidacy, Graduate, Junior Plus, Non-Degree or Senior Plus.Students in a Non-Degree Undergraduate degree may not enroll.
